# Include Directory

This directory contains the project header files for the ESP32 quadruped robot firmware.

A header file contains C/C++ declarations and macro definitions shared between several source files. You request the use of a header file in your source file by including it with the C preprocessing directive `#include`.

```cpp
// src/main.cpp

#include "config.h"
#include "hardware.h"

void setup() { ... }
void loop() { ... }
```

Including a header file produces the same results as copying its contents into each source file that needs it. With header files, related declarations appear in only one place — if they need to be changed, they can be changed once, and every file that includes them will use the new version on the next recompile.

---

## Header Files

### `config.h`
Global project configuration. Defines WiFi, Zenoh session mode, and all ROS topic key expressions (`joint_commands`, `joint_states`, `imu/data_raw`, `imu/mag`). Also includes the core Arduino and networking libraries (`WiFi.h`, `WiFiManager.h`, `Preferences.h`, `Wire.h`).

### `hardware.h`
Hardware abstraction layer. Defines the `Leg` struct, which groups three `PCA9685Servo` joints (HAA, HFE, KFE) per leg, and the `ServoParams` namespace with the PCA9685 channel assignments for all twelve joints across the four legs. Declares the global `pwm` driver, the four `Leg` instances, the `joint_states` matrix, and the `IMUMPU9250` IMU object.

### `PCA9685.h`
Servo driver wrapper around `Adafruit_PWMServoDriver`. The `PCA9685Servo` class handles conversion from radians (or degrees) to PWM ticks at 100 Hz, with configurable per-joint travel limits. The `PCA9685Cfg` namespace holds the timing constants (`min_us`, `max_us`, `period_us`, `ticks_per_us`).

### `IMUMPU9250.h`
IMU driver for the MPU-9250. Exposes `measure` (x/y/z float triplet) and `IMUdata` (accel, gyro, mag) structs. The `IMUMPU9250` class provides `begin()`, `calibrate()`, `calibrateMag()`, and individual `getAccel()` / `getGyro()` / `getMag()` methods. Calibration constants are in the `IMUCfg` namespace.

### `mailbox.h`
FreeRTOS inter-task communication interface. Declares the `Queues` namespace with the four `QueueHandle_t` objects used to pass data between tasks: `joint_states_queue`, `time_stamp_queue`, `encoder_data_queue`, and `imu_data_queue`.

### `tasks.h`
Declarations for all FreeRTOS tasks and the Zenoh data handler callback: `readEncodersTask`, `readIMUTask`, `writeServosTask`, `sendStatusTask`, `watchdogTask`, and `data_handler`.

### `utilities.h`
Helper functions for serialization, deserialization, and networking. Includes `deserializeJointStates()`, `serializeImu()`, `serializeMag()`, `serializeJointStates()`, `getPreciseTime()`, and `beginNetwork()`. Uses `ucdr/microcdr.h` for CDR-based ROS 2 message encoding.

### `zenoh.h`
Zenoh-pico session interface. Declares the global session object (`z_owned_session_t`), the joint-states subscriber (`z_owned_subscriber_t`), and the three publishers for IMU, magnetometer, and encoder data.

### `ServoCtrl.h`
Legacy servo driver using the ESP32 LEDC peripheral directly via GPIO pins. Superseded by `PCA9685.h` but kept for reference. The `ServoCtrl` class and `ServoCfg` namespace mirror the PCA9685 interface at 50 Hz.

---

## Dependency Graph

```
config.h
└── (WiFi, WiFiManager, Preferences, Wire, Arduino)

hardware.h
├── PCA9685.h
│   └── Adafruit_PWMServoDriver
└── IMUMPU9250.h
    └── config.h

mailbox.h
└── FreeRTOS (queue.h)

tasks.h
└── zenoh.h
    └── zenoh-pico

utilities.h
├── ucdr/microcdr.h
└── IMUMPU9250.h
```

---

For more on header files see the official GCC documentation:
https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/cpp/Header-Files.html